{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Motif discovery"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pylab as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar.distance import matrix_profile\n",
    "from wildboar.annotate import motifs, regimes\n",
    "from wildboar.utils.plot import plot_time_domain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we download and load a dataset from the web."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = np.loadtxt(\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=1DYG3rwW_zpd-7lcgYeL0Y2nHtkr2Fi0O\")\n",
    "x = x[20000:30000]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we compute the matrix profile with a window size of 200 timesteps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mp, mpi = matrix_profile(x, window=200, return_index=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we plot the time series (top) and the matrix profile (bottom)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<AxesSubplot:>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=2, figsize=(12, 4), sharex=True)\n",
    "plot_time_domain(x, ax=ax[0])\n",
    "plot_time_domain(mp, ax=ax[1])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we find the top motifs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "motif_ind = motifs(\n",
    "    x,\n",
    "    mp=mp,\n",
    "    max_distance=0.5,\n",
    "    max_motif=6,\n",
    "    min_neighbours=2,\n",
    "    max_neighbours=5,\n",
    "    exclude=0.2,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And, plot the motifs and their neighbors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 4), sharex=True)\n",
    "plot_time_domain(x, ax=ax)\n",
    "cmap = plt.get_cmap(\"Dark2\", 3)\n",
    "for c, ind in enumerate(motif_ind):\n",
    "    for i in ind:\n",
    "        ax.plot(np.arange(i, i + 200), x[i : i + 200], color=cmap(c))"
   ]
  }
 ],
